{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1309,"text":"As a singer-songwriter,"},{"time":3412,"text":"people often ask me about my influences\nor, as I like to call them,"},{"time":7151,"text":"my sonic lineages."},{"time":9563,"text":"And I could easily tell you"},{"time":11215,"text":"that I was shaped by the jazz\nand hip hop that I grew up with,"},{"time":14659,"text":"by the Ethiopian heritage of my ancestors,"},{"time":17994,"text":"or by the 1980s pop\non my childhood radio stations."},{"time":21783,"text":"But beyond genre,\nthere is another question:"},{"time":25398,"text":"how do the sounds we hear every day\ninfluence the music that we make?"},{"time":30547,"text":"I believe that everyday soundscape"},{"time":32624,"text":"can be the most unexpected\ninspiration for songwriting,"},{"time":36089,"text":"and to look at this idea\na little bit more closely,"},{"time":38628,"text":"I'm going to talk today\nabout three things:"},{"time":40773,"text":"nature, language and silence --"},{"time":43821,"text":"or rather, the impossibility\nof true silence."},{"time":47827,"text":"And through this I hope to give you\na sense of a world"},{"time":50381,"text":"already alive with musical expression,"},{"time":53456,"text":"with each of us serving\nas active participants,"},{"time":57461,"text":"whether we know it or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60136,"text":"I'm going to start today with nature,\nbut before we do that,"},{"time":62978,"text":"let's quickly listen to this snippet\nof an opera singer warming up."},{"time":66602,"text":"Here it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68700,"text":"(Singing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83910,"text":"(Singing ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85571,"text":"It's beautiful, isn't it?"},{"time":88201,"text":"Gotcha!"},{"time":89376,"text":"That is actually not the sound\nof an opera singer warming up."},{"time":93161,"text":"That is the sound of a bird"},{"time":95684,"text":"slowed down to a pace"},{"time":97630,"text":"that the human ear mistakenly\nrecognizes as its own."},{"time":102012,"text":"It was released as part of Peter Szöke's\n1987 Hungarian recording"},{"time":106840,"text":"\"The Unknown Music of Birds,\""},{"time":109246,"text":"where he records many birds\nand slows down their pitches"},{"time":113141,"text":"to reveal what's underneath."},{"time":115615,"text":"Let's listen to the full-speed recording."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119650,"text":"(Bird singing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123638,"text":"Now, let's hear the two of them together"},{"time":125574,"text":"so your brain can juxtapose them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128167,"text":"(Bird singing at slow then full speed)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146338,"text":"(Singing ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150063,"text":"It's incredible."},{"time":151864,"text":"Perhaps the techniques of opera singing\nwere inspired by birdsong."},{"time":156880,"text":"As humans, we intuitively understand birds\nto be our musical teachers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162439,"text":"In Ethiopia, birds\nare considered an integral part"},{"time":165367,"text":"of the origin of music itself."},{"time":168542,"text":"The story goes like this:"},{"time":171538,"text":"1,500 years ago, a young man\nwas born in the Empire of Aksum,"},{"time":176595,"text":"a major trading center\nof the ancient world."},{"time":179525,"text":"His name was Yared."},{"time":182402,"text":"When Yared was seven years old\nhis father died,"},{"time":185634,"text":"and his mother sent him to go live\nwith an uncle, who was a priest"},{"time":189281,"text":"of the Ethiopian Orthodox tradition,"},{"time":191600,"text":"one of the oldest churches in the world."},{"time":194892,"text":"Now, this tradition has an enormous amount\nof scholarship and learning,"},{"time":198377,"text":"and Yared had to study and study\nand study and study,"},{"time":201413,"text":"and one day he was studying under a tree,"},{"time":204053,"text":"when three birds came to him."},{"time":207321,"text":"One by one, these birds\nbecame his teachers."},{"time":210912,"text":"They taught him music -- scales, in fact."},{"time":215579,"text":"And Yared, eventually\nrecognized as Saint Yared,"},{"time":218106,"text":"used these scales to compose\nfive volumes of chants and hymns"},{"time":222568,"text":"for worship and celebration."},{"time":224764,"text":"And he used these scales\nto compose and to create"},{"time":228177,"text":"an indigenous musical notation system."},{"time":231645,"text":"And these scales evolved\ninto what is known as kiñit,"},{"time":235292,"text":"the unique, pentatonic, five-note,\nmodal system that is very much alive"},{"time":241209,"text":"and thriving and still evolving\nin Ethiopia today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246531,"text":"Now, I love this story because\nit's true at multiple levels."},{"time":249718,"text":"Saint Yared was a real, historical figure,"},{"time":252765,"text":"and the natural world\ncan be our musical teacher."},{"time":257057,"text":"And we have so many examples of this:"},{"time":259235,"text":"the Pygmies of the Congo\ntune their instruments"},{"time":261482,"text":"to the pitches of the birds\nin the forest around them."},{"time":264396,"text":"Musician and natural soundscape\nexpert Bernie Krause describes"},{"time":267598,"text":"how a healthy environment\nhas animals and insects"},{"time":270996,"text":"taking up low, medium\nand high-frequency bands,"},{"time":274448,"text":"in exactly the same way\nas a symphony does."},{"time":278066,"text":"And countless works of music\nwere inspired by bird and forest song."},{"time":282972,"text":"Yes, the natural world\ncan be our cultural teacher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288751,"text":"So let's go now to the uniquely\nhuman world of language."},{"time":293083,"text":"Every language communicates\nwith pitch to varying degrees,"},{"time":296351,"text":"whether it's Mandarin Chinese,"},{"time":297813,"text":"where a shift in melodic inflection\ngives the same phonetic syllable"},{"time":301829,"text":"an entirely different meaning,"},{"time":303610,"text":"to a language like English,"},{"time":304976,"text":"where a raised pitch\nat the end of a sentence ..."},{"time":307370,"text":"(Going up in pitch) implies a question?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309412,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311045,"text":"As an Ethiopian-American woman,"},{"time":312728,"text":"I grew up around the language\nof Amharic, Amhariña."},{"time":315160,"text":"It was my first language,\nthe language of my parents,"},{"time":317663,"text":"one of the main languages of Ethiopia."},{"time":320716,"text":"And there are a million reasons\nto fall in love with this language:"},{"time":323934,"text":"its depth of poetics,\nits double entendres,"},{"time":326799,"text":"its wax and gold, its humor,"},{"time":329440,"text":"its proverbs that illuminate\nthe wisdom and follies of life."},{"time":334038,"text":"But there's also this melodicism,\na musicality built right in."},{"time":338734,"text":"And I find this distilled most clearly"},{"time":340633,"text":"in what I like to call\nemphatic language --"},{"time":343130,"text":"language that's meant\nto highlight or underline"},{"time":345390,"text":"or that springs from surprise."},{"time":348036,"text":"Take, for example, the word: \"indey.\""},{"time":351204,"text":"Now, if there are Ethiopians\nin the audience,"},{"time":353330,"text":"they're probably chuckling to themselves,"},{"time":355361,"text":"because the word means\nsomething like \"No!\""},{"time":357469,"text":"or \"How could he?\" or \"No, he didn't.\""},{"time":359304,"text":"It kind of depends on the situation."},{"time":361429,"text":"But when I was a kid,\nthis was my very favorite word,"},{"time":365304,"text":"and I think it's because it has a pitch."},{"time":368721,"text":"It has a melody."},{"time":369956,"text":"You can almost see the shape\nas it springs from someone's mouth."},{"time":372981,"text":"\"Indey\" -- it dips, and then raises again."},{"time":376391,"text":"And as a musician and composer,\nwhen I hear that word,"},{"time":379504,"text":"something like this\nis floating through my mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383982,"text":"(Music and singing \"Indey\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393832,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":396711,"text":"Or take, for example, the phrase\nfor \"It is right\" or \"It is correct\" --"},{"time":400726,"text":"\"Lickih nehu ... Lickih nehu.\""},{"time":402322,"text":"It's an affirmation, an agreement."},{"time":404979,"text":"\"Lickih nehu.\""},{"time":406161,"text":"When I hear that phrase,"},{"time":407337,"text":"something like this starts rolling\nthrough my mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412031,"text":"(Music and singing \"Lickih nehu\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419572,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422199,"text":"And in both of those cases,\nwhat I did was I took the melody"},{"time":425040,"text":"and the phrasing\nof those words and phrases"},{"time":427523,"text":"and I turned them into musical parts\nto use in these short compositions."},{"time":432539,"text":"And I like to write bass lines,"},{"time":434044,"text":"so they both ended up\nkind of as bass lines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437387,"text":"Now, this is based on the work\nof Jason Moran and others"},{"time":440037,"text":"who work intimately\nwith music and language,"},{"time":443099,"text":"but it's also something I've had\nin my head since I was a kid,"},{"time":446067,"text":"how musical my parents sounded"},{"time":448122,"text":"when they were speaking\nto each other and to us."},{"time":452070,"text":"It was from them\nand from Amhariña that I learned"},{"time":454468,"text":"that we are awash in musical expression"},{"time":457372,"text":"with every word,\nevery sentence that we speak,"},{"time":460011,"text":"every word, every sentence\nthat we receive."},{"time":462787,"text":"Perhaps you can hear it\nin the words I'm speaking even now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468237,"text":"Finally, we go to the 1950s United States"},{"time":470676,"text":"and the most seminal work\nof 20th century avant-garde composition:"},{"time":474611,"text":"John Cage's \"4:33,\""},{"time":476759,"text":"written for any instrument\nor combination of instruments."},{"time":480912,"text":"The musician or musicians are invited\nto walk onto the stage"},{"time":484495,"text":"with a stopwatch and open the score,"},{"time":487709,"text":"which was actually purchased\nby the Museum of Modern Art --"},{"time":490664,"text":"the score, that is."},{"time":492641,"text":"And this score has not\na single note written"},{"time":496173,"text":"and there is not a single note played"},{"time":498671,"text":"for four minutes and 33 seconds."},{"time":502540,"text":"And, at once enraging and enrapturing,"},{"time":507254,"text":"Cage shows us that even\nwhen there are no strings"},{"time":510166,"text":"being plucked by fingers\nor hands hammering piano keys,"},{"time":515238,"text":"still there is music,\nstill there is music,"},{"time":517739,"text":"still there is music."},{"time":519825,"text":"And what is this music?"},{"time":522903,"text":"It was that sneeze in the back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525132,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526702,"text":"It is the everyday soundscape\nthat arises from the audience themselves:"},{"time":531787,"text":"their coughs, their sighs, their rustles,\ntheir whispers, their sneezes,"},{"time":536080,"text":"the room, the wood\nof the floors and the walls"},{"time":538645,"text":"expanding and contracting,\ncreaking and groaning"},{"time":541127,"text":"with the heat and the cold,"},{"time":542555,"text":"the pipes clanking and contributing."},{"time":547306,"text":"And controversial though it was,\nand even controversial though it remains,"},{"time":550970,"text":"Cage's point is that there is no\nsuch thing as true silence."},{"time":556107,"text":"Even in the most silent environments,\nwe still hear and feel the sound"},{"time":560636,"text":"of our own heartbeats."},{"time":562646,"text":"The world is alive\nwith musical expression."},{"time":566383,"text":"We are already immersed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570330,"text":"Now, I had my own moment of,\nlet's say, remixing John Cage"},{"time":574047,"text":"a couple of months ago"},{"time":575738,"text":"when I was standing\nin front of the stove cooking lentils."},{"time":578765,"text":"And it was late one night\nand it was time to stir,"},{"time":581931,"text":"so I lifted the lid off the cooking pot,"},{"time":583927,"text":"and I placed it onto\nthe kitchen counter next to me,"},{"time":586384,"text":"and it started to roll back and forth"},{"time":588671,"text":"making this sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592765,"text":"(Sound of metal lid\nclanking against a counter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598929,"text":"(Clanking ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601525,"text":"And it stopped me cold."},{"time":603727,"text":"I thought, \"What a weird, cool swing\nthat cooking pan lid has.\""},{"time":610200,"text":"So when the lentils were ready and eaten,"},{"time":614808,"text":"I hightailed it to my backyard studio,"},{"time":618326,"text":"and I made this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621187,"text":"(Music, including the sound\nof the lid, and singing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638271,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":640479,"text":"Now, John Cage\nwasn't instructing musicians"},{"time":642915,"text":"to mine the soundscape\nfor sonic textures to turn into music."},{"time":647060,"text":"He was saying that on its own,"},{"time":649937,"text":"the environment is musically generative,"},{"time":653422,"text":"that it is generous, that it is fertile,"},{"time":657687,"text":"that we are already immersed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660765,"text":"Musician, music researcher, surgeon\nand human hearing expert Charles Limb"},{"time":666802,"text":"is a professor at Johns Hopkins University"},{"time":668881,"text":"and he studies music and the brain."},{"time":672739,"text":"And he has a theory"},{"time":675735,"text":"that it is possible -- it is possible --"},{"time":678855,"text":"that the human auditory system\nactually evolved to hear music,"},{"time":684027,"text":"because it is so much more complex\nthan it needs to be for language alone."},{"time":689733,"text":"And if that's true,"},{"time":691532,"text":"it means that we're hard-wired for music,"},{"time":694501,"text":"that we can find it anywhere,"},{"time":696638,"text":"that there is no such thing\nas a musical desert,"},{"time":699740,"text":"that we are permanently\nhanging out at the oasis,"},{"time":703463,"text":"and that is marvelous."},{"time":706135,"text":"We can add to the soundtrack,\nbut it's already playing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710260,"text":"And it doesn't mean don't study music."},{"time":712138,"text":"Study music, trace your sonic lineages\nand enjoy that exploration."},{"time":717355,"text":"But there is a kind of sonic lineage\nto which we all belong."},{"time":722267,"text":"So the next time you are seeking\npercussion inspiration,"},{"time":724914,"text":"look no further than your tires,\nas they roll over the unusual grooves"},{"time":728287,"text":"of the freeway,"},{"time":730035,"text":"or the top-right burner of your stove"},{"time":732237,"text":"and that strange way that it clicks"},{"time":733970,"text":"as it is preparing to light."},{"time":736733,"text":"When seeking melodic inspiration,"},{"time":738369,"text":"look no further than dawn\nand dusk avian orchestras"},{"time":741885,"text":"or to the natural lilt\nof emphatic language."},{"time":745137,"text":"We are the audience\nand we are the composers"},{"time":748160,"text":"and we take from these pieces"},{"time":749979,"text":"we are given."},{"time":751154,"text":"We make, we make, we make, we make,"},{"time":753046,"text":"knowing that when it comes to nature\nor language or soundscape,"},{"time":757490,"text":"there is no end to the inspiration --"},{"time":760511,"text":"if we are listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763421,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764597,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}